  "response_text": "The commercial opens in a formal, old-fashioned banquet room. A long pale runner leads straight toward open double doors framed by draped curtains, tall potted palms, wall sconces, and a chandelier overhead. Bright light pours through the doorway from the space beyond. A well-dressed man in a black tuxedo and bow tie enters along the runner, moving briskly as if supervising preparations.\n\nAt the doorway, he meets waiters in white dinner jackets with black bow ties. One young waiter holds a large metal chafing dish or covered serving pan at chest height. The tuxedoed man leans in, lifts or checks the lid, and peers inside, carrying a light-colored folder or clipboard tucked under one arm. He smiles and gestures approvingly, then waves the waiter on. Another waiter stands behind with a tall tray or stacked serving piece. The tuxedoed man turns to him and helps guide a large tiered dessert display: a pyramid of small pale pastries or cake-like rounds on a tray, topped with a small floral decoration. He steadies the tray at the edge and looks pleased, as if making sure the centerpiece is ready before it is brought into the room.\n\nThe view returns to the wide banquet-room entrance. More staff and musicians come through the doorway. Two waiters maneuver a long rectangular table covered in a white cloth into position, one on each end. In the center foreground, a smiling bald, mustached man in a burgundy dinner jacket stands behind a black metal music stand with sheet music clipped open. Behind him, other musicians in similar burgundy jackets move into place; an upright bass is visible over one musician’s shoulder. The man at the music stand holds a baton or bow-like stick and looks forward, smiling broadly, then glances to the side as the staff continue arranging the room around him. He raises one hand high with his index finger lifted, like a conductor giving a cue. The room briefly darkens as his raised hand remains silhouetted near the bright doo